page.title: 10HOUSING-RURAL SETTING
page.content: Most of the houses are privately owned here with gardens and trees .The secondary school is surrounded with lovely playing fields and community halls .The old quarry has been filled in to make more space for houses and factories of all different kinds from a tea blenders to a tile factory which makes tiles for hospitals and floors for big offices .There aren't many shops here but most people have cars and there is a railway station and lots of buses .There is an area of houses where people who were in the Territorial Army live ,these houses all look the same .Some of the streets here are very quiet even though there are factories and buses .The factories are on a part of the district that is like a country road on a hill and hidden from view behind a beech hedge { Pages 6-10 by Carnwadric primary 5
